# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE suppression file
# One CVE ID per line. Add a comment above each entry explaining why it's suppressed.
# Review suppressions quarterly.

# CVE-2023-44487 (HTTP/2 Rapid Reset Attack)
# Mitigated at load balancer level (nginx rate limiting + connection limits).
# No fix available in current node:20-slim base image.
# Approved: zia.ullah@valueadd.se | Review: 2025-01-01
CVE-2023-44487

# ── Debian OS / base image CVEs (libcap2, libgnutls30) ──────────────────────
# These are in the node:20-slim base image OS packages, not in application code.
# GnuTLS CVEs are DTLS protocol vulnerabilities — our API is HTTP-only and does
# not use DTLS. libcap2 TOCTOU race requires local filesystem access to exploit.
# Fixed versions exist in Debian but are not yet in the node:20-slim image.
# Accepted as base-image risk; not exploitable in this application's threat model.
# Approved: zia.ullah@valueadd.se | Review: 2026-10-01

# libcap2 — Privilege escalation via TOCTOU race in cap_set_file()
CVE-2026-4878

# libgnutls30 — DoS via DTLS zero-length fragment (DTLS not used by this app)
CVE-2026-33845

# libgnutls30 — Authentication bypass via NUL character in username (DTLS only)
CVE-2026-42010

# libgnutls30 — DoS via heap buffer overflow in DTLS handshake (DTLS not used)
CVE-2026-33846

# libgnutls30 — Policy bypass via case-sensitive nameConstraints comparison
CVE-2026-3833

# libgnutls30 — DoS via DTLS packet reordering (DTLS not used by this app)
CVE-2026-42009

# ── npm bundled toolchain CVEs (not application code) ───────────────────────
# All CVEs below are in npm's own internal packages located at
# /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/ — these are npm's build tools,
# not runtime dependencies of this application. The running container does not
# execute npm after startup; these packages have zero exposure at runtime.
# Our application's own dependencies (app/node_modules/) are clean (0 CVEs).
# Approved: zia.ullah@valueadd.se | Review: 2026-10-01

# cross-spawn (npm internal) — ReDoS via crafted shell argument
CVE-2024-21538

# glob (npm internal) — Command injection via malicious filenames
CVE-2025-64756

# minimatch (npm internal) — DoS via crafted glob patterns (3 variants)
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# sigstore (npm internal) — Unauthorized certificates due to ignored OIDs option
CVE-2026-48815

# tar (npm internal) — Arbitrary file overwrite/traversal via malicious archives
# npm uses tar for package extraction at install time only, not at runtime
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802
